reviewText:
This game has a typical single plotline, with your average cut-scene/screen text narrative. However, this plotline is a product of a professional story writer, so this linearity does not bother you. Besides, the game has so much to offer!

Karma system (although it's harder to be a bad guy, well, the devs are german, so I can see why);
Trading system, sophisticated just enough to not to get boring;
A very beatiful graphical design - hold Q and make some wallpapers!
Diverse in-game moneymaking - fight pirates, be a pirate, trade, smuggle, accomplish a variety of missions...
Interesting upgrade system - brings some RPG element into the game. And the game really benefits from it!

Weak sides of DSO in my opinion, are:
Small room for maneuver during combat - makes all non-cruiser fights pretty straightforward;
Useless minimap;
Very small HP indicator when playing 1080p;
Bad controller support.

